  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 9 for SLE 12 SP3)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.4.114-94_14 fixes one issue.\n\nThe following security issue was fixed:\n\n- CVE-2018-5391: Fixed a possible denial of service attack with low rates of specially modified packets targeting IP fragment re-assembly. An attacker may cause a denial of service condition by sending specially crafted IP fragments. The current vulnerability (CVE-2018-5391) became exploitable in the Linux kernel with the increase of the IP fragment reassembly queue size (bsc#1103098).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
